ZH: 我喜欢旁听别人上课。
EN: I enjoy auditing other people's classes.

ZH: 他去年旁听了一门法律课程。
EN: He audited a law course last year.

ZH: 旁听是一种学习的好方式。
EN: Auditing is a great way to learn.

ZH: 她经常请人来旁听她的讲座。
EN: She often invites people to audit her lectures.

ZH: 我们可以旁听这个会议吗？
EN: Can we audit this meeting?

ZH: 旁听者需要提前向教授申请。
EN: Auditors need to apply in advance to the professor.

ZH: 我打算明年选课时旁听一门心理学课程。
EN: I plan to audit a psychology course when I enroll next year.

ZH: 他已经旁听过这门课三次了。
EN: He has audited this course three times already.

ZH: 旁听者可以参与讨论吗？
EN: Can auditors participate in the discussion?

ZH: 我对这门课感兴趣，但不打算接受正式考核，所以我选择旁听。
EN: I'm interested in this course, but I don't intend to undergo formal assessment, so I'm choosing to audit.

ZH: 旁听学生也可以使用图书馆资源。
EN: Auditing students can also use the library resources.

ZH: 旁听不需要完成作业。
EN: Auditing doesn't require completing assignments.

ZH: 他在大学期间旁听了一系列艺术课程。
EN: He audited a series of art courses during his time at university.

ZH: 旁听可以帮助我了解不同学科的内容。
EN: Auditing can help me understand the content of different subjects.

ZH: 我希望通过旁听加深对法律的理解。
EN: I hope to deepen my understanding of law through auditing.

ZH: 旁听可以提供我没有时间修读的课程知识。
EN: Auditing can provide me with knowledge of courses I don't have time to take.

ZH: 学校允许学生旁听其他专业的课程。
EN: The school allows students to audit courses from other majors.

ZH: 旁听者应该尊重其他学生的学习空间。
EN: Auditors should respect the learning space of other students.

ZH: 旁听并不会被计入学分。
EN: Auditing does not count towards credits.

ZH: 我想尝试旁听一门外语课，以提高我的口语能力。
EN: I want to try auditing a foreign language course to improve my speaking skills.
